<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-617-731  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 617 731.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Robotics and Automation  Oct 1990 v6 n5p522(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fast collision avoidance for manipulator arms: a sequential searchstrategy. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gupta, Kamal Kant.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A novel sequential strategy to plan collision-free motions for amanipulator arm is given.andP;  The strategy is based on the idea ofplanning the motion of each link successively, starting from thebase link.andP;  Tests show the strategy quickly finds a collision-freepath in a large number of situations.andP;  The strategy can be used toform a front end to other motion planning algorithms.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AlgorithmsRobotsManipulatorsSearch StrategyCollision Detection.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Decomposing the motion problem. (chart)Single-link problem. (chart)Geometric illustration for terms used in deriving the contactangles. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>